<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 14 at 7:09PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...PATCHY BLACK ICE AND SLIPPERY ROADS TONIGHT...
With temperatures expected to drop into the 10s overnight, any
untreated surfaces may become slippery due to the snow that fell
during the snow squalls/showers earlier today. Patchy black ice
is also possible due to the refreezing of melted snow. Motorists
are urged to use caution if traveling tonight.</description>
